            <h3 class=""medium_heading""> II. PEDAGOGICAL OBJECTIVES    </h3>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 1. Origin of the program   </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The mining and quarries sector plays a fundamental role in the economic development of countries. About two-thirds of the African continent
                    countries concentrate mining activities and more than half produce minerals for the international market. It alone can account for up to 25% of a
                    states’ GDP. Due to the increasing demand for metals from emerging countries (doubling the urban population, developing infrastructure at a
                    steady pace), the sector’s future prospects are promising. 	
 ");
            WriteLiteral(@"                   
                    With a view to sustainable business growth, mining companies are increasingly looking for solutions and a skilled workforce to manage the
                    social and environmental impacts of their activities: pollution, population displacement etc 	
                    
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 2. Objectives of the program   </h3>
                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.1. General objective </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The objective of the Master in Civil Engineering-Sustainable Mining Management is to train professionals capable of identifying, evaluating and
                    minimizing the environmental impacts of quarries and mines.                     
                </p>

                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.2. Specific Objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
   ");
            WriteLiteral(@"                 <strong> Commun run to the mention </strong><br/>
                   At the end of this program, the student will be able to: <br/>
                    <ul class=""one_list"">
                        <li> 
                            Know how to evaluate the risks related to the mining of a given site, 	
                        </li>
                        <li> 
                            Know how to handle and/or minimize risks when they intervene (mining waste, mine water, air releases, etc..), 	
                        </li>
                        <li> 
                            Control the legislation and framework of the mineral economy,
                        </li>
                        <li> 
                            Use environmental assessment tools and conduct an environmental audit of a quarry or mining site, 	
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II.3. Program approach </h");
